---
import Site from '../../layouts/Site.astro';
---

<Site title="The Lawyer — matter-centric AI legal assistant">
	<section style="padding: 2rem 0; text-align: center;">
		<h1 style="font-size: 2.4rem; letter-spacing: -0.03em;">The Lawyer</h1>
		<p style="max-width: 40rem; margin: 1rem auto 0; color: var(--muted); font-size: 1.1rem;">
			An AI assistant organized the way a practice is: around matters. It dockets deadlines, runs
			conflict checks at intake, drafts from your clause library, tracks billable time, and files
			every document on the matter — with an audit trail behind every action.
		</p>
		<div style="margin-top: 1.75rem;">
			<a class="btn" href="/pricing">See pricing</a>
			<a class="btn ghost" href="/docs/the-lawyer/getting-started" style="margin-left: 0.5rem;">Get started</a>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section style="margin-top: 2.5rem; display: grid; gap: 1rem; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(16rem, 1fr));">
		<div style="border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem;">
			<h3 style="font-size: 1rem;">Docketing that reminds</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">Mention a court date in chat and it's docketed with two-stage reminders. Nothing lives in anyone's memory.</p>
		</div>
		<div style="border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem;">
			<h3 style="font-size: 1rem;">Conflicts at intake</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">Conflict checks against every recorded party before a matter opens, with a tamper-evident attestation chain.</p>
		</div>
		<div style="border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem;">
			<h3 style="font-size: 1rem;">Drafting from your standards</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">Your clause library and negotiation playbook — the assistant drafts from them, reviews against them, and files the PDF on the matter.</p>
		</div>
		<div style="border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem;">
			<h3 style="font-size: 1rem;">Ethical walls that hold</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">A walled matter vanishes from every tool, tab, and search for everyone outside the wall — wildcard permissions or not.</p>
		</div>
		<div style="border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem;">
			<h3 style="font-size: 1rem;">Time and pre-bills</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">"Log half an hour on Vandelay" is a time entry. Pre-bills export to PDF, filed on the matter for review.</p>
		</div>
		<div style="border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.25rem;">
			<h3 style="font-size: 1rem;">Client intake over WhatsApp</h3>
			<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem;">Clients message like they already do; intake lands in the matter workspace with documents attached.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section style="margin-top: 3rem; border: 1px solid var(--line); border-radius: 0.75rem; padding: 1.5rem; background: var(--surface);">
		<h2 style="font-size: 1.2rem;">Not legal advice — leverage</h2>
		<p style="color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.95rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
			Every draft is a starting template for attorney review. The assistant never invents statutes
			or citations, flags anything outside your library as new language, and recommends review by
			a licensed attorney — by design, in its instructions, on every matter.
		</p>
	</section>
</Site>
